Name: Blackeye
Breeder: Div. of Hort., Central Expt. Farm, Ottawa, Ont., Canada.
Characteristics: vegetable soybean, excellent for freezing green, home garden and field production for shelled green beans.
Adaptation: wide regional. Div. of Hort. Ottawa, Prog. Rpt. 1934-48. p. 61.
Parentage: selection from material introduced from Manchuria.

Name: Kahala (288 BB 4-6-3-3)
Breeder: Univ. Hawaii Agric. Expt. Sta., Honolulu.
Vendor: Univ. Hawaii Agric. Expt. Sta., Honolulu.
Characteristics: vigorous, leafy plant, pods held high.
Adaptation: tropical and subtropical climates. Hawaii Agric. Expt. Sta. Research Rpt. 178. 1969.

Name: Kaikoo (288 BB 24-9-3-6)
Breeder: Univ. of Hawaii Agric. Expt. Sta., Honolulu.
Vendor: Univ. of Hawaii Agric. Expt. Sta., Honolulu.
Characteristics: white flowered; pods held high on plant; grows on cultivar of soils.
Adaptation: tropical and subtropical climates. Hawaii Agr. Expt. Sta. Res. Rpt. 178. 1969.

Name: Kailua (288 BB 4-7-1-3)
Breeder: Univ. of Hawaii Agr. Expt. Sta., Honolulu.
Vendor: Univ. of Hawaii Agr. Expt. Sta., Honolulu.
Characteristics: dark-green foliage, white flowers, pods easy to pick.
Adaptation: tropical and subtropical climates. Hawaii Agr. Expt. Sta. Research Rpt. 178. 1969.

Name: Mokapu Summer (288 BC 28-1-2-2)
Breeder: Univ. of Hawaii Agr. Expt. Sta., Honolulu.
Vendor: Univ. of Hawaii Agr. Expt. Sta., Honolulu.
Characteristics: purple flowers, large pod and seed, good flavor; for summer harvest.
Adaptation: tropical and subtropical climates. Hawaii Agr. Expt. Sta. Res. Rpt. 178. 1969.

Name: Pando (Panda in England)
Breeder: Dept. of Hort., Univ. of New Hampshire, Durham.
Characteristics: extremely early-neutral edible cultivar maturing dry seeds in 75 days on plants 1 foot tall.
Adaptation: general regional, but will mature even in the far northern United States. 1952.
Parentage: unknown, collected in city market, Seoul, Korea, July 4. 1947.
